    "updated_at": "2015-08-12T19:41:50Z",
    "body": "I\u2019m still a bit uncomfortable by the fact that we do not allow inner mutability in this particular Mutex. You\u2019d usually won\u2019t want to Mutex-guard immutable data because it is, well, immutable and in most cases is already MT-safe, and mutable ReentrantMutex ready to share and use looks a little bit odd/redundant: `Arc<ReentrantMutex<RefCell<T>>>`.\n",
